/*!
\page elementary_dec2hex DEC2HEX Convert Decimal Number to Hexadecimal

<p>
Section: \ref sec_elementary "Elementary Functions"
\section Usage
Converts an integer value into its hexadecimal representation.  The syntax
for its use is
\verbatim
   y = dec2hex(x)
\endverbatim
where <tt>x</tt> is an integer (and is promoted to a 64-bit integer if it is not).
The returned value <tt>y</tt> is a string containing the hexadecimal representation
of that integer.  If you require a minimum length for the hexadecimal
representation, you can specify an optional second argument
\verbatim
   y = dec2hex(x,n)
\endverbatim
where <tt>n</tt> indicates the minimum number of digits in the representation.
\section Example
